OL,3,CJail for killer who punched 'kind and
OL,4,Chonest' engineer at Christmas party
OL,6,FA pub-goer has been jailed for 10
OL,7,Fyears after killing a "much loved"
OL,8,Fgrandfather with a punch outside a pub.
OL,10,FNathan Gothard caused 66-year-old
OL,11,FDavid Darke serious head injuries as
OL,12,Fhe fell backwards onto the ground.
OL,14,FMr Darke had been to a work Christmas
OL,15,Fdinner and then drinks at the Crown
OL,16,FInn in Appleby Magna, Leicestershire,
OL,17,Fon 21 December last year. He died in
OL,18,Fhospital six days later.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G1/8
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,378,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37702
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F377A1779555957
OL,3,CJail for killer who punched 'kind and
OL,4,Chonest' engineer at Christmas party
OL,6,FGothard, 37, of Church Street, was
OL,7,Fcleared of murder but found guilty of
OL,8,Fmanslaughter after a trial. He was
OL,9,Fsentenced to 10 years on Friday.
OL,11,FThe court heard there was a dispute as
OL,12,FGothard had been "making unwelcome
OL,13,Fadvances and remarks" to women in the
OL,14,Fgroup, and making clear the pub was
OL,15,F"his terrain".
OL,17,FThe pub owners escorted Gothard out,
OL,18,Fbut he returned and there was a fight.
OL,20,FMr Darke then helped Gothard up, when
OL,21,Fhe was punched, the jury was told.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G2/8
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,378,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F377A1779555957
OL,3,CJail for killer who punched 'kind and
OL,4,Chonest' engineer at Christmas party
OL,6,FMr Darke's family said as Gothard was
OL,7,Fsentenced: "Our family has finally
OL,8,Fseen the person responsible for Dave's
OL,9,Fdeath sentenced. Although the sentence
OL,10,Fshows some accountability, no sentence
OL,11,Fwill ever truly reflect what has been
OL,12,Ftaken from us.
OL,14,F"Gothard was a braggart whose local
OL,15,Fpub Dave's colleagues visited after
OL,16,Ftheir works Christmas meal. Dave's
OL,17,Fonly 'crime' that night was stepping
OL,18,Fin the way of a thug intent on
OL,19,Fharassing the women and antagonising
OL,20,Fthe men in the group.
OL,26,@vD@AOU
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G3/8
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,378,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37704
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F377A1779555957
OL,3,CJail for killer who punched 'kind and
OL,4,Chonest' engineer at Christmas party
OL,6,F"Dave was a much-loved father,
OL,7,Fbrother, grandfather, and friend.
OL,9,F"He was a strong, fit, hardworking man
OL,10,Fwho lived honestly and treated people
OL,11,Fwith respect.
OL,13,F"He was an accomplished craftsman who
OL,14,Fcould turn his hand to anything, and
OL,15,Fthere was very little he could not fix
OL,16,For build.
OL,18,F"He had always worked hard and was
OL,19,Flooking forward to retirement and
OL,20,Fenjoying the next chapter of life with
OL,21,Fhis family.
OL,26,@nD@AOU
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G4/8
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,378,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37705
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F377A1779555957
OL,3,CJail for killer who punched 'kind and
OL,4,Chonest' engineer at Christmas party
OL,6,F"What makes this even harder to accept
OL,7,Fis that it was completely avoidable.
OL,8,FIf Gothard had simply gone home when
OL,9,Fhe was told to, Dave would still be
OL,10,Fhere today.
OL,12,F"Instead, we have had to endure the
OL,13,Funimaginable. We watched Dave's life
OL,14,Fsupport being turned off and then sat
OL,15,Fthrough a trial with every painful
OL,16,Fdetail of his final hours repeated in
OL,17,Fcourt. No family should ever have to
OL,18,Fexperience that.
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@AOU
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G5/8
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,378,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37706
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F377A1779555957
OL,3,CJail for killer who punched 'kind and
OL,4,Chonest' engineer at Christmas party
OL,6,F"Dave continued to help others.
OL,7,FThrough organ donation, at least four
OL,8,Fpeople have been given a chance of
OL,9,Flife. That says everything about the
OL,10,Fkind of man he was ` even in death, he
OL,11,Fgave to others."
OL,13,FGothard claimed he was acting in self-
OL,14,Fdefence after Mr Darke grabbed him and
OL,15,Fthreatened to kill him.
OL,17,FHe told the court he felt "ridiculed"
OL,18,Fby the group.
OL,26,@nD@AOUyD@[OUyD@eO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G6/8
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,378,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37707
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F377A1779555957
OL,3,CJail for killer who punched 'kind and
OL,4,Chonest' engineer at Christmas party
OL,6,FDetective Inspector Kevin Hames, from
OL,7,Fthe Leicestershire Police, said:
OL,8,F"Gothard had every opportunity to walk
OL,9,Faway but he chose to remain outside
OL,10,Fthe pub and his actions that day have
OL,11,Fdevastated a family.
OL,13,F"They will now need to navigate their
OL,14,Flives without their loved one. On
OL,15,Fbehalf of the team, I would like to
OL,16,Fthank them for their courage and
OL,17,Funderstanding."
OL,26,@pD@AOUuD@AOUyD@OO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G7/8
